text: Herb Naismith (9 October 1915 – 17 June 1995) is a former Australian rules footballer who played with Collingwood in the Victorian Football League (VFL). His father Wally Naismith, and uncle Charlie Naismith, also played in the VFL. == Notes == == External links == * * *Herb Naismith's profile at Collingwood Forever Category:1915 births Category:1995 deaths Category:Australian rules footballers from Victoria (Australia) Category:Collingwood Football Club players
